Package: tovid
Architecture: all
Section: contrib/graphics
Priority: optional
XB-Python-Version: ${python:Versions}
Depends: mplayer-nogui | mplayer, mencoder, mjpegtools, normalize-audio,
 imagemagick, ffmpeg, transcode, sox, ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: dvdauthor (>=0.6.11), vcdimager, lsdvd, libdvdcss2
Suggests: cdrdao, libdvdread3, dvd+rw-tools,
 pytovid (= ${Source-Version}), tovid-gui (= ${Source-Version}),
 python-libtovid (= ${Source-Version})
Description: Console utils for making (S)VCDs and DVDs (bash version)
 Tovid can help you create your own DVDs, VCDs, and SVCDs for
 playback on your home DVD player.
 .
 tovid converts arbitrary video formats into (S)VCD/DVD-compliant MPEG
 files, and can help with menu creation and disc authoring. Other tools
 included can:
   * make animated menus
   * identify audio and video codecs in nearly any file
   * shrink MPEG videos
 .
 This package contains these bash CLI scripts:
   * idvid -- identifies audio and video codecs in a video
   * makedvd -- authors and burns DVDs
   * makemenu -- creates menus for (S)VCDs and DVDs
   * makevcd -- authors and burns (S)VCDs
   * makexml -- creates xml control files for (S)VCDs and DVDs
   * postproc -- adjusts MPEG videos: shrinking, audio synchronizing
   * todisc -- creates SVCDs and DVDs with animated menus
   * tovid -- converts arbitrary video files to (S)VCD or DVD MPEG files
   * tovid-batch -- converts multiple video files for (S)VCD or DVD
   * tovid-interactive -- a CLI wizard for tovid
 .
 Homepage: http://tovid.wikia.com

