Package: pytovid
Architecture: all
Section: contrib/graphics
Priority: optional
XS-Python-Version: >= 2.4
XB-Python-Version: ${python:Versions}
Depends: python (>= 2.4), python-libtovid (= ${Source-Version})
Recommends: tovid (= ${Source-Version})
Suggests:
Description: Console utils for making (S)VCDs and DVDs (python version)
 Tovid can help you create your own DVDs, VCDs, and SVCDs for
 playback on your home DVD player.
 .
 tovid converts arbitrary video formats into (S)VCD/DVD-compliant MPEG
 files, and can help with menu creation and disc authoring.
 .
 This package contains these python implementations of the tovid bash
 scripts:
   * pyidvid -- identifies audio and video codecs in a video
   * pymakemenu -- creates menus for (S)VCDs and DVDs
   * pymakexml -- creates xml control files for (S)VCDs and DVDs
   * pytovid -- converts arbitrary video files to (S)VCD or DVD MPEG files
   * tovid-stats -- displays conversion history (time, bitrate, size, ...)
 .
 Homepage: http://tovid.wikia.com

